# Summary
This page explains behavioral cohorts in Amplitude, which are groups of users with similar behaviors defined by actions taken within specific time periods. It covers how to create cohorts through the Cohort tab or Microscope, import cohorts from files, compare cohorts, and use them for segmentation across Amplitude charts and analyses.

